+# Sario - Super Mario Bros Clone
# Makefile for building with SDL2

CC = gcc
CFLAGS = -Wall -Wextra -O2 `sdl2-config --cflags`
LDFLAGS = `sdl2-config --libs`

SRCDIR = src
INCDIR = include
BUILDDIR = build

SOURCES = $(SRCDIR)/main.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/game.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/player.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/level.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/entities.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/collision.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/graphics.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/input.c \
          $(SRCDIR)/physics.c

OBJECTS = $(SOURCES:$(SRCDIR)/%.c=$(BUILDDIR)/%.o)
TARGET = sario

.PHONY: all clean run

all: $(TARGET)

$(TARGET): $(OBJECTS)
	$(CC) $(OBJECTS) -o $@ $(LDFLAGS)

$(BUILDDIR)/%.o: $(SRCDIR)/%.c | $(BUILDDIR)
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -I$(INCDIR) -c $< -o $@

$(BUILDDIR):
	mkdir -p $(BUILDDIR)

clean:
	rm -rf $(BUILDDIR) $(TARGET)

run: $(TARGET)
	./$(TARGET)

*** Add File: README.md
+# Sario
+
+A Super Mario Bros clone written in C using SDL2.
+
+## Description
+
+Sario is a side-scrolling platformer that recreates the classic World 1-1 level from Super Mario Bros on the NES. The game features:
+
+- Classic Mario-style physics and controls
+- Tile-based level design
+- Enemy AI (Goombas)
+- Power-ups (Mushrooms)
+- Interactive blocks (Question blocks, breakable bricks)
+- Scrolling camera
+- Score, coins, and timer system
+- Lives and game over mechanics
+- Victory condition (reach the flag)
+
+## Requirements
+
+- GCC or Clang compiler
+- SDL2 development libraries
+- Linux/Unix environment (or WSL on Windows)
+
+### Installing SDL2 (Debian/Ubuntu)
+```bash
+sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev
+```
+
+### Installing SDL2 (Arch Linux)
+```bash
+sudo pacman -S sdl2
+```
+
+### Installing SDL2 (Fedora)
+```bash
+sudo dnf install SDL2-devel
+```
+
+## Building
+
+```bash
+make
+```
+
+## Running
+
+```bash
+make run
+# or
+./sario
+```
+
+## Controls
+
+| Key | Action |
+|-----|--------|
+| Arrow Left / A | Move Left |
+| Arrow Right / D | Move Right |
+| Space / Z / Up / W | Jump |
+| Enter | Start Game / Confirm |
+| Escape | Quit |
+
+## Game Mechanics
+
+### Player
+- **Small Sario**: One hit = death
+- **Big Sario** (after mushroom): One hit = shrink, invincibility frames
+- **Invincibility**: 2 seconds (120 frames) after getting hit
+
+### Enemies
+- **Goombas**: Walk back and forth, can be stomped for 100 points
+- Stomp from above to defeat, any other contact hurts you
+
+### Blocks
+- **Question Blocks**: Hit from below to get a mushroom
+- **Brick Blocks**: Break when big, otherwise just bump
+- **Hard Blocks**: Indestructible
+
+### Scoring
+- Stomp Goomba: 100 points
+- Collect Coin: 200 points
+- Hit Question Block: 100 points
+- Get Mushroom: 1000 points
+- Break Brick: 50 points
+- Time bonus: 50 points per second remaining
+
+## Level Layout
+
+The game features a recreation of World 1-1 with:
+- Starting area with question blocks
+- Three pipes of increasing height
+- Elevated platforms
+- Multiple Goomba encounters
+- Staircase sections
+- Flag pole for level completion
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```
+sario/
+├── include/
+│   └── sario.h         # Main header with all definitions
+├── src/
+│   ├── main.c          # Entry point and game loop
+│   ├── game.c          # Game state management
+│   ├── player.c        # Player physics and rendering
+│   ├── level.c         # Level data and tilemap
+│   ├── entities.c      # Enemies and items
+│   ├── collision.c     # Collision detection
+│   ├── graphics.c      # SDL2 rendering
+│   ├── input.c         # Keyboard handling
+│   └── physics.c       # Physics utilities
+├── Makefile
+└── README.md
+```
+
+## Technical Details
+
+- **Tile Size**: 16x16 pixels
+- **Screen Resolution**: 640x480
+- **Level Size**: 220 tiles wide x 15 tiles tall
+- **Physics**: Gravity-based with AABB collision
+- **Frame Rate**: V-synced (typically 60 FPS)
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+- Sound effects and music
+- More enemy types (Koopa Troopas, Lakitus)
+- Additional levels
+- Sprite-based graphics instead of colored rectangles
+- Power-ups (Fire Flower, Star)
+- Warp pipes to different areas
+- Hidden 1-up mushrooms
+- Better font rendering
